-jcl/5.3.15/src/test/java/org_springframework/spring_jcl/LogAdapterTest.java:16:    private static final String LOGGER_NAME = \"spring-jcl.dynamic-access\";\n./stats/org.apache.pekko/pekko-protobuf-v3_3/1.0.1/execution-metrics.json:4:    \"library\": \"org.apache.pekko:pekko-protobuf-v3_3:1.0.1\",\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:22:| **Repository automation (Metadata Forge)** | Generate or repair metadata using LLM-driven pipelines. | Per coordinate, the toolkit can: (1) **add support for a new library** — generate a JUnit / Kotlin / Scala test suite, scaffold metadata, and iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access is collected ([`add_new_library_support.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py)); (2) **fix a Java compilation (`javac`) failure** raised by a library version bump ([`fix_javac_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_javac_fail.py)); (3) **fix a JVM-mode (`javaTest`) runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_java_run_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_run_fail.py)); (4) **fix a `native-image` runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_ni_run.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_ni_run.py)); (5) **improve dynamic-access coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered call sites; (6) **post-generation repair** of the metadata produced by a previous run ([`fix_post_generation_pi.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_post_generation_pi.py), [`fix_metadata_codex.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_metadata_codex.py)). Each task runs Gradle tasks against a worktree of this repo, appends a schema-validated metrics record, and — when invoked through [`forge/git_scripts/make_pr_*.py`](../forge/git_scripts/) — opens a PR for human review. See [forge/docs/architecture.md](../forge/docs/architecture.md). |\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:46:- A `stats/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/stats.json` mirror of per-version metrics (dynamic-access call sites, coverage, lines of code, dependency information).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:55:- Coverage collection (JaCoCo) and dynamic-access reporting per coordinate.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:74:- `latest/badges.json` — badges shown in the README (libraries supported, tested versions, dynamic-access coverage, tested LOC).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:84:1. **Add new library support** — generate a JUnit test suite, scaffold metadata, iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access metadata is collected.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:87:4. **Improve coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered dynamic-access call sites.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:217:- **FR-T-7** Dynamic-access coverage between consecutive tested versions of a library must not regress (enforced by reviewer skills `review-fixes-javac-fail`, `review-fixes-native-image-run-fail`, `review-fixes-java-run-fail`).\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:319:  Output: `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/test/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:98:  [--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access] \\\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:123:- `--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access` keeps generated tests for dynamic-access workflows even if no dynamic-access call sites are covered.\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:383:coordinates, active dynamic-access classes, source-context paths, and Gradle\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:416:### Dynamic-access iterative workflow\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:418:The `dynamic_access_iterative` workflow improves metadata accuracy by using the `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` Gradle task to identify which dynamic-access call sites (reflection, JNI, resources, serialization) are not yet covered by the generated tests. Instead of generating tests blindly, the workflow iterates class-by-class, sending the agent targeted prompts with the exact uncovered call sites for each class. After each attempt, the report is regenerated and coverage deltas are computed to decide whether to retry the same class or move on.\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:424:Dynamic-access strategies can optionally download library source code, upstream tests, and/or documentation as read-only agent context. This is configured per strategy via the `source-context-types` parameter in `predefined_strategies.json`. Available types are `main`, `test`, and `documentation`. The artifacts are downloaded from URLs in the library's `index.json` (populated by the `populateArtifactURLs` Gradle task) and extracted to `local_repositories/source_context/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/`.\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:449:Composite strategies (run a primary workflow, then refine dynamic-access coverage):\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:456:#### Running a dynamic-access strategy\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:478:For the detailed function-level notes and sequence diagram, see `docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md`.\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:57:    \"description\": \"Dynamic-access-guided Codex workflow using downloaded main library sources as read-only context.\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:62:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:81:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:95:    \"description\": \"Dynamic-access-guided Pi workflow using downloaded main library sources as read-only context.\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:100:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:119:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:133:    \"description\": \"Dynamic-access-guided Pi workflow using downloaded main library sources as read-only context.\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:139:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:153:    \"description\": \"Dynamic-access-guided Codex workflow using downloaded upstream test sources as read-only context.\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:158:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:177:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:191:    \"description\": \"Dynamic-access-guided Codex workflow using downloaded documentation artifacts as read-only context.\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:196:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:215:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:229:    \"description\": \"Dynamic-access-guided Codex workflow using main sources plus upstream test sources.\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:234:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:254:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:269:    \"description\": \"Dynamic-access-guided Codex workflow using main sources plus documentation artifacts.\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:274:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:294:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:309:    \"description\": \"Dynamic-access-guided Codex workflow using main sources, upstream test sources, and documentation artifacts.\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:314:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:335:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:351:    \"description\": \"Dynamic-access-guided Codex workflow using upstream test sources plus documentation artifacts.\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:356:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:376:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:391:    \"description\": \"Composite strategy: runs javac_iterative to fix compilation, then improves dynamic-access coverage.\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:398:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:420:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:441:      \"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:442:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:475:    \"description\": \"Composite strategy: runs java_run_iterative to fix runtime failures, then improves dynamic-access coverage.\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:482:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynami